MME. VANDERVELDE TURNS IN FINAL GIFT; Sails Today After Collecting Nearly $300,000 for Relief in Belgium. BOY BEGS FOR A WAR SISTER Day's Receipts of the Various Agencies Collecting for European Sufferers.

Mme. Lalla Vandervelde, wife of Emile Vandervelde, the Belgian Minister of State, who sails for Europe on the Cunarder Lusitania today, called at the offices of the Commission for Relief in Belgium, 71 Broadway, yesterday, and left a check for $1,801 as the latest result of her efforts for the relief cause in which she has been engaged in the United States since last October.
